A great deal of thought and consideration was put into the design of this pistol, and all of the components selected were chosen specifically with performance and ergonomics in mind. This is NOT your neighbor's uncomfortable and clumsily slapped-together gun-show AR pistol. 

I started with a matched Spikes Tactical Jolly Roger lower and A3 upper set. This is the less common Jolly Roger with the "Parley/Plunder/Arrr" roll marks (color filled) - not the one with the boring bullet pictograms. The lower started off with a Spikes enhanced lower parts kit, but was upgraded further to include an improved trigger group, Wolff springs, and Strike Industries enhanced pivot/takedown pins.

The 10.5" Rainier Arms Match .223 Wylde barrel (.223 Rem/5.56 NATO) and Daniel Defense low profile gas block fit perfectly under the 10" full floating quad rail handguard with integrated forward QD sling point and Strike Industries Cobra forward grip.
